description: Kansas City is quite famous for their robust Barbeque scene, and thanks to the oh-so-chromatic Tito’s BBQ truck, there are now some fresh Filipino flavors in the mix. Tito Ardie (“Tito” is Tagalog for “uncle”, a title used to express respect for authority, elders, etc...) is taking his extensive experience in the hospitality industry, as well as his passion for Filipino cuisine to bring you Tito’s BBQ. Modeled after a Jeepney (a common and colorful mode of transportation in the Philippines), this festive truck is where you’ll find a succulent selection of meat skewers that are marinated and grilled to perfection. Tito is also serving up other authentic fare, like lumpia (tasty filipino eggrolls), chicken empanadas, siopao (pork stuffed steamed buns), and so much more. If you’re looking for delightful fun and deliciousness at your next event, just know that Tito’s cuisine is perfect for every type of party!
name: Tito's BBQ
